11. VERIFIED CREATOR STATUS
11.1 You may apply to become a verified creator and obtain status as a verified creator (
“Verified Creator Status”
). To obtain Verified Creator Status, all connected social accounts must be public and have 100+ followers, 15 pieces of content (80% original), and be active for over 6 weeks. Accounts that do not meet these requirements will be ineligible to become verified creators on the WeAre8 App.
11.2 We reserve the right to deny Verified Creator Status to any individual whose social accounts may cause a threat to Brands or Citizens, as determined by us in our sole discretion. This includes (but is not limited to) accounts which include any content or materials that:
11.2.1 violate any intellectual property laws;
11.2.2 is defamatory, pornographic, illegal, or offensive in nature;
11.2.3 is used to sell illegal property; or
11.2.4 depicts hatred, violence, cruelty, or anything else that could in our reasonable opinion constitute hate speech, infringe the rights of others, or be otherwise considered illegal, immoral, distressing or offensive (including but not limited to abuse, threats, obscenity, defamation, libel, or otherwise promote illegal activities or conduct) or is in our reasonable opinion inappropriate (including but not limited to nudity, bullying, excessive violence, selling firearms, drugs or excessive alcohol, and vulgar speech (verbal and written)).
11.3 The application process involves connecting your social network accounts and going through both automatic and manual verification process. You will be notified if you are approved. Any content in relation to your social network accounts must comply with the rules and restrictions as set out in clause 13.2 and 13.3 below.
12. MODERATION OF THE WEARE8 APP
12.1. These terms govern the use of our content moderation services across images, text, usernames, and videos. By using our platform, you agree to comply with these guidelines and acknowledge that we aim to create a safe, respectful, and inclusive environment for all users. This section outlines the moderation principles and guidelines that we apply to maintain the integrity of our platform.
12.2. Image Moderation Guidelines: We aim to ensure that image content on our platform adheres to safety standards while respecting the diversity of users.
12.2.1.Prohibited Content:
12.2.1.1 Explicit Content: This includes visible or obstructed genitalia, buttocks, female nipples (excluding through clothing), and sexual activity (excluding kissing).
12.2.1.2 Violence and Weapons: Graphic depictions of real-world violence or weapons are prohibited, though artistic or gaming-related depictions may be evaluated in context.
12.2.1.3 Self-Harm and Gore: Explicit depictions of self-harm or excessive blood and gore are prohibited.
12.2.1.4 Hate Symbols and Extremism: Content containing Nazi symbols, white supremacy symbols, extremist material, or promoting terrorism is prohibited.
12.2.1.5 Animal Cruelty: Any depiction of animal cruelty will be rejected.
12.2.2 Acceptable Content:
12.2.2.1 Content that adheres to appropriate guidelines, including art, history, education, or entertainment, may be allowed depending on context.
12.2.2.2 Brief accidental exposure or non-gratuitous depictions are handled leniently, especially in artistic, cinematic, or educational contexts.
12.3. Text Moderation Guidelines: We strive to foster open discussion while ensuring that comments remain respectful, inclusive, and constructive.
12.3.1 Prohibited Comments:
12.3.1.1 Profanity: Comments that use profanity to insult or attack others will be rejected.
12.3.1.2 Hate Speech: Comments promoting hate speech or discriminating against any group will be rejected.
12.3.1.3 Personal Insults: Attacks against individuals or groups are prohibited.
12.3.2 Acceptable Comments:
12.3.2.1 Profanity used in a positive or constructive manner is allowed.
12.3.2.2 Comments expressing differing opinions, when done respectfully, are welcome.
12.4. First Name Moderation Guidelines: First names are an essential part of a user’s identity. We aim to allow cultural diversity while maintaining respect for all users.
12.4.1 Prohibited Names:
12.4.1.1 First names containing explicit profanity or offensive language.
12.3.1.2 Strings of random characters, symbols, emojis, or numbers that do not resemble real names.
12.4.2 Acceptable Names:
12.4.2.1 Common and traditional first names from various cultures.
12.4.2.2 Unusual names that are legitimate or publicized.
12.4.2.3 Names that may have different meanings in other languages but are not offensive in the user’s context.
12.5 Last Name Moderation Guidelines: Last names are an important part of user identity. We aim to support a respectful platform while accommodating diverse naming practices.
12.5.1 Prohibited Last Names:
12.5.1.1 Names containing explicit profanity or offensive language.
12.5.1.2Strings of random characters, symbols, emojis, or numbers that do not resemble real surnames.
12.5.2 Acceptable Last Names:
12.5.2.1 Common, traditional, and hyphenated last names from a variety of cultures.
12.5.2.2 Surnames that might be misinterpreted in one context but are legitimate in another.
12.6 Username Moderation Guidelines: Usernames are public identifiers and are visible to all users. They play a key role in maintaining a safe and welcoming environment.
12.6.1 Prohibited Usernames:
12.6.1.1 Usernames containing explicit profanity, sexual references, or promoting illegal activities.
12.6.1.2 Usernames that contain hate speech or discriminatory content.
12.6.2 Acceptable Usernames:
12.6.2.1 Usernames related to gaming or internet culture references.
12.6.2.2 Creative usernames that do not violate other guidelines.
12.6.2.3 Usernames with numbers, special characters, or combinations that do not present offensive material.
12.7 Video Moderation Guidelines: We ensure video content is analyzed objectively and in line with our safety standards.
12.7.1 Prohibited Video Content:
12.7.1.1 Explicit Content: This includes visible genitalia, buttocks, female nipples (excluding through clothing), and sexual activity (excluding kissing).
12.7.1.2 Violence and Weapons: Graphic depictions of real-world violence or visible weapons are prohibited.
12.7.1.3 Self-Harm and Gore: Depictions of self-harm or excessive blood and gore are rejected.
12.7.1.4 Extremist Content: Videos promoting terrorism, hate speech, or extremist ideologies will be rejected.
12.7.1.5 Animal Cruelty: Explicit depictions of animal cruelty are not allowed.
12.7.1.6 Drug Use: Videos showing explicit drug use are prohibited.
12.7.2 Acceptable Video Content:
12.7.2.1 Artistic, Cinematic, and Educational Content: Videos within these categories may be evaluated leniently, provided they are non-gratuitous.
12.7.2.2 Contextual Factors: Educational, historical, or documentary content may be allowed if factual and non-exploitative.
12.7.2.3 Accidental Exposure: Brief accidental exposure may be considered differently than intentional violations.
12.8. Moderation Process and Decision Making
12.8.1 Decision Making: Our moderators will review content based on the guidelines above. Content will either be Allowed or Rejected based on the presence of prohibited material and the overall context.
12.8.2 Holistic Evaluation: Moderators will take into account the full context of the content, including its intent, purpose, tone, and setting. Special considerations are given to artistic, educational, and historical content when appropriate.
12.9 Special Considerations
12.9.1 Cultural Sensitivity: Names, images, and content from different cultures and languages will be assessed with respect for their meanings and contexts.
12.9.2 Accidental Exposure: Minor accidental violations (e.g., brief accidental nudity) will be evaluated leniently based on the overall context and intent of the content.
12.9.3 Non-Exploitative Content: Educational, historical, or documentary content is allowed if it is factual, non-exploitative, and serves a legitimate purpose.12.10. Enforcement and Consequences
12.10.1 Violation of Guidelines: Content that violates these guidelines will be rejected. Repeated violations may lead to account suspension or permanent bans, depending on the severity of the infractions.
12.10.2 Appeals: Users may appeal moderation decisions by submitting a formal request through the platform’s support system.
12.11 Updates and Amendments: These Terms of Use may be updated from time to time. Users will be notified of significant changes and are encouraged to review the guidelines regularly to stay informed of any updates.By continuing to use the platform, you agree to adhere to these Terms of Use and the associated moderation guidelines.
12.12 In our sole discretion, select posts from Verified Creators will be approved to appear on the 8Stage. You will receive a notification if your post is selected.
